=H= Commands

Create session:         ‹tmux new -s <name>›
List sessions:          ‹tmux ls›
Attach to session:      ‹tmux attach -t <name>›
Kill session:           ‹tmux kill-session -t <name>›
Rename session:         ‹tmux rename-session -t <old> <new>›

=H= Keybindings

=h= Session management

‹prefix d ›           - Detach from current session

‹prefix s ›           - List sessions
‹prefix $ ›           - Rename current session

=h= Window management

‹prefix c ›           - Create new window
‹prefix $ ›           - Kill current window

‹prefix n ›           - Switch to next window
‹prefix p ›           - Switch to previous window
‹prefix <number> ›    - Switch to <number> window

‹prefix w ›           - List windows
‹prefix , ›           - Rename current window

=h= Pane management

‹prefix " ›           - Split horizontally (top/bottom)
‹prefix % ›           - Split vertically (left/right)
‹prefix ! ›           - Break the pane into new window
‹prefix x ›           - Kill the pane

‹prefix { ›           - Swap the pane with the previous one
‹prefix } ›           - Swap the pane with the next one
‹prefix C-<arrow> ›   - Resize the pane (step = 1 cell)
‹prefix M-<arrow> ›   - Resize the pane (step = 5 cells)
‹prefix z ›           - Zoom the pane

‹›                    Switch to layout:
‹prefix M-1 ›         - Even-horizontal
‹prefix M-2 ›         - Even-vertical
‹prefix M-3 ›         - Main-horizontal
‹prefix M-4 ›         - Main-vertical
‹prefix M-5 ›         - Tiled

‹prefix <arrow> ›     - Move between panes (by arrow keys)
‹prefix ; ›           - Toggle between the current and previous pane

‹prefix q ›           - Show pane numbers

=h= Copy mode

‹prefix [ ›           - Enter copy mode
‹q ›                  - Exit copy mode
‹Space ›              - Start selecting
‹Enter ›              - Copy selected text
‹prefix ] ›           - Paste

=h= Other

‹prefix t ›           - Show time

=h= Custom

‹prefix v ›           - Set session working dir to current pane dir

‹prefix b ›           - Toggle status bar visibility

‹prefix k ›           - Kill current session

‹Ctrl+Shift+<arrow> › - Move window to the left (right)
‹prefix j-<number> ›  - Move pane to <number> window
‹prefix a <number> ›  - Swap the pane by number

‹M-<arrow> ›          - Go to <arrow> pane
